import asyncio
from concurrent.futures import ThreadPoolExecutor

import fused
import nest_asyncio
from shapely.geometry import Polygon

nest_asyncio.apply()

# Call UDF
async def process_tile(layer):
    # Run UDF
    TOKEN = "50328bf70ab299512ce70897d1c26e4cdb0f0978aab45d8b65b95a34bf0edf18"
    return await fused.run(
        TOKEN,
        engine='realtime',
        x=9, y=5, z=4,
        layer=layer,
        sync=False
        )


async def process_tiles_parallel(layers):
    dfs = []
    with ThreadPoolExecutor(max_workers=10) as executor:
        loop = asyncio.get_event_loop()
        futures = [loop.run_in_executor(executor, process_tile, layer) for layer in layers]
        for future in await asyncio.gather(*futures):
            dfs.append(await future)
    return dfs

# Process the tiles in parallel for each layer
async def main():
    return await process_tiles_parallel(LAYERS)

# Run the asynchronous function
out = asyncio.run(main())
